{{Infobox body of water | name=Lagoa Azul | image = Sao Tome Blue Lagoon 4.jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = Northwestern [[Lobata District]], [[São Tomé Island|São Tomé]], [[São Tomé and Príncipe]] | coords = {{coord|0.4063|6.6103|region:ST_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Sao Tome | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = Lagoa Azul at the north of São Tomé Island | type = bay | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = | length = | width = | area = | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }}
'''Lagoa Azul''' (Portuguese for "blue lagoon") is a small bay in the northern part of the island of [[São Tomé Island|São Tomé]] in [[São Tomé and Príncipe]]. It is part of the [[Parque Natural Obô de São Tomé]].<ref name="ST">{{cite web|url=https://arleciosoares13.wordpress.com/areas-protegidas/parque-natural-de-sao-tome/|title=Parque Natural d'Obô em São Tomé|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref> It is 4 km northwest of the town [[Guadalupe, São Tomé and Príncipe|Guadalupe]]. It is a popular spot for [[Underwater diving|diving]].<ref>[http://costanorte.pt/pt/ilhas-de-stome/13/2-lagoa-azul/ Lagoa Azul]</ref> There is a [[Lagoa Azul Lighthouse|lighthouse]] near the bay, built in 1997.<ref name=rowlett>{{cite rowlett|stp|accessdate= 1 November 2018}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Geography of São Tomé and Príncipe]]
