==Historical flags==
=== Flags of Thailand ===
{| class="wikitable" |- ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="250"|Use!!width="250"|Description |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand (Ayutthaya period).svg|150px]] || c. 1700–1782 || Ensign of [[Siam]] || A red plain rectangular flag. |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand (1782).svg|150px]] || 1782-1817 || State ensign of Siam || Red flag with a white [[Sudarshana Chakra|chakra]]. |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand (1817).svg|150px]] || 1817–1843<ref>[https://drive.google.com/file/d/181F5jH2Bq6sQJg3n3j_rKQ9W_bBcQu4h/view Supplement of The Singapore Free Press 26th October 1843]</ref> || State ensign of Siam || Red flag with a [[white elephant (pachyderm)|white elephant]] inside the chakra. |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand 1855.svg|150px]] || 1843<ref>[https://drive.google.com/file/d/181F5jH2Bq6sQJg3n3j_rKQ9W_bBcQu4h/view Supplement of The Singapore Free Press 26th October 1843]</ref>–1916 || Flag of Siam || A [[white elephant (pachyderm)|white elephant]] facing to the hoist in the red flag. Called in [[Thai language]] "''Thong Chang''{{-"}} (ธงช้างเผือก)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rbvex.it/asiapag/thailandia.html |title=Siam Bandiera mercantile 1839 |accessdate=2004-09-25 |author=Roberto Breschi|coauthors= |language=Italian |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20041208223916/http://www.rbvex.it/asiapag/thailandia.html |archivedate= 8 December 2004}}</ref> (the elephant flag). |- | [[File:State Flag of Thailand (1916).svg|150px]] || 1916–1917 || State flag and ensign of Siam || Red flag with a white elephant in regalia. |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand (1916).svg|150px]] || 1916–1917 || Current civil flag and former ensign of Siam || Five horizontal stripes flag like the "''Trairanga''{{-"}} but the middle stripe is red. |- | [[File:Flag of Thailand (non-standard colours 2).svg|150px]] || 1917–2017|| Last flag of Siam and current flag of Thailand ||Five horizontal stripes of red, white, blue, white and red, the middle stripe twice as wide as the others.<ref>{{cite web|title=พระราชบัญญัติแก้ไขพระราชบัญญัติธง พ.ศ. ๒๔๖๐|url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2460/A/436.PDF}}</ref>. |}
===Naval [[Jack (flag)|jacks]]=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="250"|Use!!width="250"|Description |- | [[File:Naval Ensign of Siam (1881-1887).svg|150px]] || 1881-1897 || Naval Ensign of Siam || Red flag with a white elephant in regalia, with a white Chakra at the top corner. |- | [[File:State Flag of Thailand (1916).svg|150px]] || 1898–1912 || Naval Ensign of Siam || Red flag with a white elephant in regalia. |- | [[File:Naval Ensign of Siam (1910-1917).svg|150px]] || 1912–1917 || Naval Ensign of Siam || Red flag with a white elephant in regalia, with the emblem of the Royal Thai Navy at the top corner. |- | [[File:Naval Jack of Siam (1855).svg|150px]] || 1855–1881 || Naval Jack of Siam || Blue flag with a white elephant. |- | [[File:Naval Jack of Siam (1881-1917).svg|150px]] || 1881–1917 || Naval Jack of Siam || Blue flag with a white elephant in regalia. |}
===War flags=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="250"|Use!!width="250"|Description |- |[[File:Flag of the Siamese Expeditionary Force in World War I (Obverse).svg|150px]]||1917–1918|| Standard of the [[Siamese Expeditionary Force]], Obverse || Triranga defaced with a red disc containing dressed white elephant, facing a flagpole. Briefly, its appearance is the same as naval ensign, but both red banners of the flag contains a stanza from a Buddhist chant in Pali, written in Thai script: "พาหุํสหัส์สมภินิม์มิตสาวุธัน์ตํ ค๎รีเมขลํอุทิตโฆรสเสนมารํ ทานาทิธัม์มวิธินาชิตวามุนิน์โท ตัน์เตชสาภวตุเมชยสิทธินิจ์จํ". |- |[[File:Flag of the Siamese Expeditionary Force in World War I (Reverse).svg|150px]]||1917–1918|| Standard of the [[Siamese Expeditionary Force]], Reverse || Triranga defaced with a red disc containing King [[Vajiravudh]]'s personal emblem. The emblem features Thai acronym "ร.ร." and Thai digit six ("๖"), both are displayed under the glowing crown. Both red banners of the flag contains the same chant in Thai script as the obverse. |}
