{{Waikato-geo-stub}}

'''Okuryangava''' is a suburb of [[Windhoek]], the capital of [[Namibia]]. The township is situated in the north of the town between the suburbs of Freedomland, Golgota and Ombili in [[Katutura]] in Khomas region of Namibia. Okuryangava is divided into different sections, to mention a few: 74, 79, Women Center, Orieta, Monte christo
(bus loading zone), Stop and shop. It is also known for the two service stations and has schools such as [[Tobias Hainyeko Primary School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=29405&page=archive-read|title=Bus drivers desert Monte Christo for Okuryangava|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observer.com.na/business/126-dbn-finances-okuryangava-bakery|title=DBN finances Okuryangava bakery - Windhoek Observer|first=Staff|last=Reporter|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://economist.com.na/2473/general-news/fresh-n-bake-expands-operations/|title=Fresh n’ Bake expands operations|publisher=}}</ref>

