This is a list of the '''Flags of the [[Sri Lanka]]n [[Provinces of Sri Lanka|Provinces]]'''. Provincial [[flag]]s for the modern provinces of Sri Lanka were first introduced in 1987, and 1988 for the [[North Eastern Province (Sri Lanka)|North Eastern Province]], which was at the time one entity. In 2007 with the separation of the North Eastern Province, into the [[Northern Province, Sri Lanka|Northern]] and the [[Eastern Province, Sri Lanka|Eastern]] provinces, two new flags were adopted.

Most of the flags are based upon ancient [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] flags, and or symbols for their respective regions.<ref>{{cite web|last=Macdonald|first=Ian|title=Sri Lankan Provincial Flags|url=http://flagspot.net/flags/lk-.html|publisher=FOTW|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref> 

